Loading libraries

Disclaimer: This notebook uses missingo python library for a very nice way to visualize the distribution of NaN values.
Missingno is a Python library and compatible with Pandas.
To solved the ModuleNotFoundError install the libary using Anaconda prompt with the following command:

conda install -c conda-forge/label/gcc7 missingno

Filling in missing values

To fill in missing values I am going to use KNNimputer.
It is a more useful method which works on the basic approach of the KNN algorithm rather than the naive approach of filling all the values with mean or the median.
In this approach, we specify a distance from the missing values which is also known as the K parameter. The missing value will be predicted in reference to the mean of the neighbours.

In [38]:
from sklearn.impute import KNNImputer

col_nutrition = data.filter(regex=("100g")).columns

X = data[col_nutrition]

# define imputer
imputer = KNNImputer(n_neighbors=5, weights='uniform', metric='nan_euclidean')
In [39]:
# fit
imputer.fit(X)
